1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:55,010 --> 00:01:57,680
Whoa, that scared me...

3
00:01:58,970 --> 00:02:01,730
You pirates sure know some funny tricks!

4
00:02:01,730 --> 00:02:04,020
Teach me how to do it too!

5
00:02:05,310 --> 00:02:06,060
Huh?

6
00:02:06,810 --> 00:02:09,280
Um... Hello?

7
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:11,360
What?!

8
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:13,320
Wh-Wh-Wh-Wh-What?!

9
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:15,160
Ace!

10
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:16,950
What happened?!

11
00:02:16,950 --> 00:02:20,080
We were having a blast
until just a second ago!

12
00:02:20,950 --> 00:02:22,210
Wait, are you d–

13
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:28,210
Stay with me, Aaace!

14
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:32,970
I dozed off.

15
00:02:32,970 --> 00:02:36,010
Don't freak me out like that!
I thought you were dead!

16
00:02:36,010 --> 00:02:38,390
Ah, my bad. Sorry about that.

17
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:41,890
I was really worried about you!

18
00:02:42,890 --> 00:02:46,020
Well, whatever... Should we call it a night?

19
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:48,270
You seem really tired...

20
00:02:48,270 --> 00:02:50,070
What do you mean, Yamato?!

21
00:02:50,070 --> 00:02:52,650
We've still got a lot to talk about!

22
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:57,280
I gotta go back to my crew in the morning.

23
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:59,870
It'd be a waste to sleep tonight.

24
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,160
In that case, don't fall asleep again!

25
00:03:05,160 --> 00:03:07,040
I said I was sorry...

26
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:09,290
Now, where were we?

27
00:03:09,290 --> 00:03:12,050
You were talking about
your younger brother again!

28
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:17,430
And you were talking about
how much you wanna be Oden again!

29
00:03:18,050 --> 00:03:19,350
Not exactly, Ace.

30
00:03:19,350 --> 00:03:22,100
I don't just "want to," I will become him!

31
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:24,810
I'll make it happen for sure.

32
00:03:24,810 --> 00:03:26,560
Because this right here...

33
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:28,400
is the story of our future!

34
00:03:30,690 --> 00:03:31,820
D?

35
00:03:35,320 --> 00:03:39,570
I never thought I'd be able to meet you!

36
00:03:40,030 --> 00:03:42,290
"O-Oden"...

37
00:03:42,910 --> 00:03:44,910
Is that my father's journal?!

38
00:03:45,460 --> 00:03:51,500
It contains every detail about his grand life
and the world he experienced!

39
00:03:52,630 --> 00:03:56,300
On that day, I found it at
the river below Oden Castle.

40
00:03:57,050 --> 00:04:00,640
Someone in the castle
must have kept it from burning...

41
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:02,260
Lord Oden's...

42
00:04:03,890 --> 00:04:05,220
Momonosuke!

43
00:04:06,350 --> 00:04:10,190
He wrote a lot about you as well.

44
00:04:12,230 --> 00:04:15,110
You were born on Whitebeard's ship, right?!

45
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:17,240
And then you went on to Roger's ship!

46
00:04:18,490 --> 00:04:19,780
Mm-hmm.

47
00:04:20,410 --> 00:04:26,700
Th-Though, since I was so young,
I do not remember much...

48
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:29,960
Whitebeard, Roger, and Oden...

49
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:31,290
They all said...

50
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:34,500
that twenty years in the future,

51
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:39,260
the New World was sure to be overrun
by young and powerful pirates!

52
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:40,720
That future is now!

53
00:04:45,470 --> 00:04:49,140
I was sure that Ace would be
among them, leading the pack...

54
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:54,270
But when he died, I remembered...

55
00:04:55,110 --> 00:04:56,570
something from that night!

56
00:04:59,570 --> 00:05:00,200
What...?

57
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:04,160
Crap!

58
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,740
I let it slip!

59
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:08,450
I wasn't supposed to say that!

60
00:05:08,450 --> 00:05:10,160
You didn't hear that! Forget about it!

61
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:12,710
And don't you dare laugh either!

62
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:14,790
Sabo and I won't stand for it!

63
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:19,510
I haven't left this country even once...

64
00:05:19,510 --> 00:05:23,800
so I haven't seen much with my own eyes...

65
00:05:24,390 --> 00:05:28,930
including Ace's brother
and the world Oden traveled.

66
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:33,150
But, at that moment...

67
00:05:33,150 --> 00:05:35,110
I saw something clearly!

68
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:37,820
That's at the end...

69
00:05:38,190 --> 00:05:39,820
of my kid brother's dream.

70
00:05:44,070 --> 00:05:46,580
We gotta set out to sea someday!

71
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:50,580
Let's get out of this country and live free!

72
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:55,880
I wanna see the world out there
and write a book about it!

73
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:58,880
Navigation is the one thing I do love to study!

74
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:02,050
Let's get even stronger
and become pirates someday!

75
00:06:04,300 --> 00:06:07,510
That was my plan anyway!
You don't have to tell me twice!

76
00:06:07,930 --> 00:06:14,060
When I'm a pirate, I'll beat up everyone
and become the biggest, baddest one of all!

77
00:06:14,060 --> 00:06:17,270
That's how I'll leave my mark on the world!

78
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:23,150
It doesn't matter if the whole world
rejects or despises me,

79
00:06:23,530 --> 00:06:26,280
I'll become a great pirate and show them all!

80
00:06:27,580 --> 00:06:31,500
The government is telling us
not to go to the final island,

81
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:34,370
which is said to contain treasure untold!

82
00:06:35,330 --> 00:06:38,790
That makes it all the more tantalizing!

83
00:06:39,170 --> 00:06:42,800
If we can reach it, we will be,
in both name and in deed...

84
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:45,260
the world's greatest pirate crew!

85
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:47,510
The world's greatest?

86
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:51,220
I got it!

87
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:53,390
Alright then...!

88
00:06:53,390 --> 00:06:55,060
That's right!

89
00:06:55,060 --> 00:06:56,730
And then...

90
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:02,530
– I'll...
– I'm gonna...!

91
00:07:06,780 --> 00:07:09,660
Man, I was wondering what you would say...

92
00:07:09,660 --> 00:07:11,660
That's just a child's fantasy!

93
00:07:13,410 --> 00:07:15,920
You're a riot, Luffy!

94
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:19,040
I can't wait to see what future you is like!

95
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:32,100
Sure, we laughed when Luffy
told us, but that's okay!

96
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:35,480
We're the only ones
who are allowed to laugh...

97
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,100
'cause we believe in him!

98
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:40,860
We really think he can do it, so–

99
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:41,860
Ace!

100
00:07:43,730 --> 00:07:44,490
Huh?

101
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,490
Hey!

102
00:07:46,490 --> 00:07:47,990
What's wrong, Yamato?

103
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:53,700
I won't laugh!

104
00:07:54,580 --> 00:07:58,290
Those were the Pirate King's exact words!

105
00:07:58,290 --> 00:08:01,090
The very words that stunned Oden!

106
00:08:02,090 --> 00:08:07,300
In Kozuki Oden's journal, there was
a great man who said the same thing!

107
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:08,930
I'd never laugh at that!

108
00:08:08,930 --> 00:08:10,930
Your brother is incredible!

109
00:08:12,810 --> 00:08:14,430
A great man, huh?

110
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:15,930
Good to hear!

111
00:08:15,930 --> 00:08:19,400
Maybe Luffy and I can grab
a drink with him someday!

112
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:22,610
I'm sure you guys would get along!

113
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,570
But he's already dead.

114
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:25,650
He is?!

115
00:08:27,190 --> 00:08:30,490
Well, in that case, it'd be hard to see him...

116
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:32,490
Hey...

117
00:08:32,990 --> 00:08:34,490
What do you want now?

118
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:36,370
Well...

119
00:08:36,370 --> 00:08:38,460
How about me instead?

120
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:42,290
You, your brother, and me!

121
00:08:42,290 --> 00:08:45,050
That is... if I'm able to set sail one day...

122
00:08:45,050 --> 00:08:46,670
Sounds like fun!

123
00:08:46,670 --> 00:08:47,670
Really?!

124
00:08:47,670 --> 00:08:50,680
But you know how big
the sea is, right, Yamato?

125
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:54,430
If you don't hurry, who knows
if we'll ever see each other again–

126
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:55,430
Then, Ace,

127
00:08:55,430 --> 00:08:57,680
could you please give me...

128
00:08:57,680 --> 00:08:59,480
a strand of hair or a nail?

129
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,770
Huh?!

130
00:09:00,770 --> 00:09:03,270
Either one will work!

131
00:09:03,270 --> 00:09:04,270
Sure...

132
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:06,570
Huh?

133
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:12,570
It's done!

134
00:09:12,570 --> 00:09:13,240
Oh?

135
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,200
This is your vivre card!

136
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,950
This is it?

137
00:09:19,710 --> 00:09:21,290
It's just some paper.

138
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:27,090
Yeah! But this piece of paper will
bring us together again one day!

139
00:09:27,090 --> 00:09:28,420
Bring us together?

140
00:09:29,090 --> 00:09:29,970
Watch!

141
00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:40,060
Give a piece to anyone you want
to keep track of or meet again.

142
00:09:40,730 --> 00:09:41,600
Okay!

143
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,480
I'll be sure to do that.

144
00:09:59,250 --> 00:10:00,660
Yamato!

145
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:05,880
Don't go losing it!

146
00:10:22,270 --> 00:10:24,940
Ace!

147
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:34,110
Yamato?!

148
00:10:38,490 --> 00:10:40,580
We will meet again one day!

149
00:10:40,950 --> 00:10:43,540
Ace!

150
00:10:51,170 --> 00:10:53,170
You bet!

151
00:11:00,060 --> 00:11:01,060
In reality...

152
00:11:01,970 --> 00:11:04,020
that would be our final meeting.

153
00:11:13,070 --> 00:11:15,860
That stupid son of mine is at it again...

154
00:11:15,860 --> 00:11:20,700
Whatever. Thanks to Red Hair's little
interruption, I have some time to kill.

155
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:24,250
I can deal with the brat's temper tantrum.

156
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:31,920
You promised me... that you would return...!

157
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:39,850
It doesn't matter what hope he clings on to.

158
00:11:55,860 --> 00:11:59,030
He'll always be trapped...

159
00:11:59,030 --> 00:12:00,740
on this island.

160
00:12:06,660 --> 00:12:09,210
I can't get off of this island!

161
00:12:09,210 --> 00:12:12,670
I can't beat my father!

162
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:17,550
I can't go and rescue...

163
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:21,260
my one and only friend...!

164
00:12:22,010 --> 00:12:23,430
I'm...

165
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:27,350
not free...

166
00:12:28,890 --> 00:12:31,310
Why shackle your heart as well?!

167
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:34,480
I only want to...

168
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:37,780
live as free as Oden did...

169
00:12:38,780 --> 00:12:40,070
Ace...

170
00:12:42,410 --> 00:12:45,790
Twenty years from now,

171
00:12:45,790 --> 00:12:52,000
a group of young and powerful pirates
shall start a new era in the New World!

172
00:12:52,420 --> 00:12:56,510
But the toughest one of all
will set sail in a few years...

173
00:12:57,050 --> 00:12:59,220
My kid brother!

174
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:05,510
Go home, Yamato.

175
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,230
I'll wait, too...

176
00:13:09,690 --> 00:13:12,560
For whatever Kozuki Oden was waiting for...

177
00:13:13,190 --> 00:13:15,650
Please come back, Young Master Yamato!

178
00:13:16,030 --> 00:13:18,780
I'll wait for the new era...

179
00:13:18,780 --> 00:13:20,070
for as long as it takes!

180
00:13:21,410 --> 00:13:22,780
Luffy...

181
00:13:22,780 --> 00:13:24,740
I'll be waiting for you!

182
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:26,950
I'll keep fighting until then!

183
00:13:28,450 --> 00:13:31,170
If you still don't get it
after how many times I've told you...

184
00:13:31,670 --> 00:13:35,500
I'll just keep on beating it into you, Yamato!

185
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:38,760
And I'll keep beating this into you!

186
00:13:47,310 --> 00:13:48,970
That's the spirit, Yamato!

187
00:13:48,970 --> 00:13:53,770
I'm Oden, you rotten excuse for a father!

188
00:13:56,900 --> 00:14:02,280
I had no idea what was happening
in the outside world that day,

189
00:14:02,910 --> 00:14:05,740
but I read about it in the newspaper later.

190
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:10,870
I learned that Ace was the son of
the Pirate King, Gol D. Roger...

191
00:14:11,620 --> 00:14:16,340
and that his younger brother
had really made a name for himself!

192
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:19,300
That was Luffy, the man you brought!

193
00:14:21,170 --> 00:14:22,550
Momonosuke.

194
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:27,390
I return this to you, of course.

195
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:32,310
This is what Oden wrote about the future...

196
00:14:32,310 --> 00:14:32,350
This is what Oden wrote about the future...

197
00:14:32,350 --> 00:14:32,430
This is what Oden wrote about the future...

198
00:14:32,430 --> 00:14:32,480
This is what Oden wrote about the future...

199
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:32,520
This is what Oden wrote about the future...

200
00:14:36,020 --> 00:14:38,980
"Twenty years from now,

201
00:14:42,950 --> 00:14:46,320
a group of young and powerful pirates...

202
00:14:46,950 --> 00:14:49,200
shall start a new era in the New World!

203
00:14:51,370 --> 00:14:53,290
If I die before then...

204
00:14:56,580 --> 00:14:59,920
they will be the ones to strike down Kaido!"

205
00:15:03,630 --> 00:15:06,090
The One Piece...

206
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:14,480
You guys shouldn't even dream of
being a contender for that treasure...

207
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:22,940
When are you gonna stop
pretending to be pirates?

208
00:15:22,940 --> 00:15:26,910
You were always a lousy teacher, Kaido...

209
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:28,320
Just let me handle it!

210
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:36,040
Yeah, I know, Killer...

211
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:39,380
I get how you feel...

212
00:15:40,250 --> 00:15:42,880
I've gathered a whole mountain of scrap!

213
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:49,760
Take it off my hands, you damn Emperors!

214
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:05,650
One after another!

215
00:16:05,650 --> 00:16:07,610
So reckless...

216
00:16:07,610 --> 00:16:09,740
Is your entire crew like that?

217
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:12,620
This wasn't my idea...!

218
00:16:12,620 --> 00:16:15,700
I don't see the most reckless one...

219
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,210
Where's Straw Hat?

220
00:16:22,460 --> 00:16:24,210
Now there's even more of them.

221
00:16:24,210 --> 00:16:26,590
They're the Worst Generation, aren't they?

222
00:16:26,590 --> 00:16:30,640
Whatever they are, they'll all
scatter like dust in the wind...

223
00:16:33,850 --> 00:16:38,140
None of you are strong enough
to reopen this scar!

224
00:16:41,230 --> 00:16:45,940
Slink away with your honor intact, rookies!

225
00:16:45,940 --> 00:16:48,950
Like the Red Scabbards did...

226
00:16:58,870 --> 00:17:03,040
Twenty years from now,

227
00:17:07,170 --> 00:17:14,220
a group of young and powerful pirates
shall start a new era in the New World!

228
00:17:15,850 --> 00:17:18,230
If I die before then...

229
00:17:18,230 --> 00:17:18,350
If I die before then...

230
00:17:18,350 --> 00:17:18,430
If I die before then...

231
00:17:22,350 --> 00:17:25,110
they will be the ones...

232
00:17:26,780 --> 00:17:28,740
to strike down Kaido!

233
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:31,360
And here's another one...

234
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:33,620
How about you sit back
and watch how it's done?!

235
00:17:33,620 --> 00:17:34,830
I refuse!

236
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:34,830
Same here!

237
00:17:35,490 --> 00:17:37,790
So many heads ripe for the taking!

238
00:17:40,370 --> 00:17:42,500
Straw Hat...

239
00:17:59,430 --> 00:18:00,680
Linlin!

240
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:04,440
You wanna guess what this brat
said he'd be, right to my face?!

241
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:06,940
He sure is a cheeky one...

242
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:10,940
He talked a big game to me too!

243
00:18:10,940 --> 00:18:14,570
He even destroyed my castle!

244
00:18:14,570 --> 00:18:18,080
I believe you owe me an apology, Straw Hat!

245
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:24,500
Hey, punk...

246
00:18:24,960 --> 00:18:28,800
Tell us again what you said you'll be...

247
00:18:28,800 --> 00:18:33,590
Say it to right our faces!

248
00:18:38,810 --> 00:18:42,060
We are counting on you all.

249
00:18:44,690 --> 00:18:45,850
Sir Luffy!

250
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,320
We are in your debt!

251
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:04,330
You alright, Kin'emon?

252
00:19:05,460 --> 00:19:07,750
I'm sorry...

253
00:19:08,790 --> 00:19:10,340
I took too long.

254
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:20,220
I am... chagrined...

255
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:25,480
A-Alas...

256
00:19:26,020 --> 00:19:27,810
when I pass on...

257
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:32,530
I will have nothing to show
Lord Oden but my shame!

258
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:34,740
Kin'e–

259
00:19:37,070 --> 00:19:39,950
Would you carry...

260
00:19:41,330 --> 00:19:43,750
Wano upon your back?!

261
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:46,620
I beg–

262
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:47,750
Dummy!

263
00:19:47,750 --> 00:19:49,290
Of course I will!

264
00:19:50,790 --> 00:19:52,590
It's my friends' country!

265
00:19:59,180 --> 00:20:01,430
Hey, brat!

266
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:04,770
Sir...

267
00:20:05,390 --> 00:20:06,690
Luffy...

268
00:20:07,850 --> 00:20:09,940
We are all in...

269
00:20:09,940 --> 00:20:11,020
your debt...

270
00:20:12,770 --> 00:20:13,570
Traffy!

271
